              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Original research and data studies consistently outperform other formats. Ahrefs research found that data-backed content earns links at 2-3x the rate of opinion-based articles or how-to guides. Free tools and calculators also perform very well because they earn resource-page links and bookmarks continuously.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How long does link bait take to earn links?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Most link bait starts earning links within weeks of publication if promoted properly. Strong link bait continues attracting links for 2-5 years with zero maintenance — each new article published in the niche that covers your topic becomes a new potential linker.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Do you still need outreach for link bait?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes, for the first 30-90 days. Passive link earning assumes people discover your content. Initial promotion — targeted outreach to 20-30 relevant journalists or bloggers, social sharing, and community seeding — creates the first wave of links that makes the content visible enough to earn links passively thereafter.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between link bait and the Skyscraper Technique?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Link bait is a broad category of link-attracting content. The Skyscraper Technique is a specific strategy: find existing content with many backlinks, create a significantly better version, then outreach to people linking to the original. All Skyscraper content is link bait, but not all link bait uses the Skyscraper approach.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

